        "## Authority for UAE Information Assurance (IA) Standards Development\n\nBased on a comprehensive review of the official Abu Dhabi Government knowledge base—including Procurement Standards, HR Bylaws, Procurement Manuals, and related Information Security frameworks—**the specific authority responsible for developing the overarching UAE Information Assurance (IA) Standards cannot be definitively identified.**\n\nThe available documentation pertains primarily to governance, procedures, and standards specific to the Emirate of Abu Dhabi.\n\n### 1. Scope of Documentation Review\n\nThe search focused on official Abu Dhabi governance documents, specifically covering:\n*   Abu Dhabi Procurement Standards\n*   HR Bylaws\n*   Procurement Manuals (Ariba Aligned and Business Process)\n*   Internal Information Security Frameworks\n\n### 2. Findings Related to Abu Dhabi Governance\n\nWhile the UAE IA Standards development authority remains unidentified, the governance structure for **Abu Dhabi-specific** standards and procedures is documented:\n\n| Document/Standard | Responsible Authority/Entity | Governing Body |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Abu Dhabi Procurement Standards** | Governing authority not explicitly named as the developer in the retrieved text. | Approval by **Abu Dhabi Executive Council**. |\n| **Procurement Manual (Business Process)** | **Government Procurement Office** (Issuing Authority) | Issued pursuant to the Abu Dhabi Procurement Standards. |\n\n### 3. Conclusion Regarding UAE IA Standards\n\nThe search results explicitly confirm that the documentation consulted **does not contain details regarding the national body or entity that developed the \"UAE IA Standards.\"** The references found are localized to Abu Dhabi’s internal procurement and operational compliance frameworks.\n\n**Source Citation Summary:**\n*   Information regarding the absence of the UAE IA Standards development authority was derived from analysis across the **Abu Dhabi Procurement Standards.md** and **Procurement Manual (Business Process).md** documents, as detailed in the fallback tool execution.",
